@Hatt Hanz
I certainly agree that some parts of the story are awful, believe me, I'm the one people ask to explain the KH plotline. I think we fans still don't know what a "Kingdom Hearts" is too. Like, I thought KH1, CoM, and KH2 were fine (up to a point). The story was making sense chronologically. Days is basically the other side of CoM (Sora's perspective vs Roxas's perspective). BBS's story was new and refreshing imo until they took this Xehanort thing and pushed it into maximum overdrive.

I haven't played KHx or DDD because of the console jumps, but I'm still going to play KH3 cause I wanna see how it ends. They already took 10+ years of my life, I have to see it to the end.
